Codebook for sanda_replicate.csv  SubjectID – unique subject code  prop_stroop – total proportion of correct responses on the Stroop task  propcongruent_stroop – total proportion of correct responses on the congruent trials of the Stroop task  propincongruent_stroop – total proportion of correct responses on the incongruent trials of the Stroop task  RTcongruent_stroop – mean reaction time for correct responses on the congruent trials of the Stroop task  RTincongruent_stroop – mean reaction time for correct responses on the incongruent trials of the Stroop task  logRTcongruent_stroop – natural log of RTcongruent_stroop  logRTincongruent_stroop – natural log of RTincongruent_stroop  Stroopindex – executive function measure calculated by: logRTcongruent_stroop - logRTincongruent_stroop  HiStroopindex – Stroopindex recentered at 1SD above grand mean  LoStroopindex - Stroopindex recentered at 1SD below grand mean  accuracy – correct (1) or incorrect (0) response on a single trial of the card-sorting task  latency – reaction time for the response on a single trial of the card-sorting task  logRT – natural log of latency  trial – contrast-coded condition label for “repeat” (-1) or “switch” (1) trial on the card-sorting task  blocknumber – contrast-coded block number of the card-sorting trial  rewardlevel – contrast-coded reward level for the card-sorting trial (-1 = “low reward”, 1 = “high reward”)  rewardorder – order in which participant completed the high and low reward blocks (-1 = low-reward first, 1 = high-reward first)  setorder – order in which participant completed the two different trial-order sets on the card-sorting task (-1 = order 1 first and order 2 second, 1 = order 2 first and order 1 second)  prop_card – total proportion correct for the card-sorting task  IMI – mean score on the intrinsic motivation index (Deci, Egharari, Patrick, & Leone, 1994) 
